{
  "stem": "3964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And during the process of the tearing down and desecrating our synagogue, we had three Torah in our ark in Gemunden, which must have been there for, I don't know, a hundred years or more.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Torahs were taken out of the synagogue and desecrated, thrown out onto the street and torn apart and walked on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When I came back-- just to put this in-- when I came back in 1945 to Gemunden after four years in concentration camp, some of these people who had helped us during these difficult days in 1938 and '39 invited me to their house.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were two women who had gone to school with my mother.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they said to me, Ludwig, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we have something for you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We have hidden it since 1938.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I'm sure you would appreciate having it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one of the women went upstairs, and brought this down for me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This is part of a Sefer Torah, which they picked up during the night of November the 8th.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were very religious Christians, knew the significance of the Torah, what it meant to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "At the risk of being caught, took it home with them and hid it till I came back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "On the back side of this piece of scroll, you will see dirt and the footsteps of the Nazis, who desecrated our, our synagogue and did this to the Torah.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I'll always keep this and remind me and my children, hopefully their children, of what had happened in Germany, that nothing was sacred.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In-- But as time went on, in 1938, when my father came back from the hospital in I believe it was the early part in December.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he recuperated.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
